# gaia-public — repo ignore rules
#
# Memory model: ADR-111 consolidates the runtime tree under `.gaia/` (the
# project-root sibling). The legacy `_memory/` tree was retired and removed
# from this repo by AF-2026-06-01-2 — gaia-public has no in-tree agent
# memory; the only `_memory/` references that remain in this file's history
# are for legacy projects targeted by the framework, not gaia-public itself.
#
# `.gaia/memory/` (the canonical runtime home post-ADR-111) is gitignored
# globally because it's runtime state — see the ".gaia/ runtime state"
# block below.

# --- GAIA runtime tree — out of git per ADR-111 -----------------------------
# Everything under .gaia/ is local runtime state generated by framework
# commands run from this repo's CWD. None of it belongs in the product source —
# EXCEPT the CI-scoped config slice below.
#
# A git negation (`!path`) cannot re-include a file once its PARENT directory is
# excluded, so we cannot write `.gaia/` then `!.gaia/ci-config.yaml`. Instead:
# allow descending into the ROOT .gaia/ only (`!/.gaia/`), re-ignore its contents
# (`/.gaia/*`), then re-include the one tracked file. The rules are ANCHORED to
# the repo root with a leading slash so nested `.gaia/` runtime dirs elsewhere in
# the tree (e.g. plugins/gaia/scripts/.gaia/) stay fully ignored by the broad
# `.gaia/` rule above.
.gaia/
!/.gaia/
/.gaia/*

# EXCEPTION: the CI-scoped config slice IS tracked. This repo's canonical
# project config lives ABOVE the checkout root at an untracked project root, so
# CI never sees it and selective tests would fall back to the full suite on
# every PR. .gaia/ci-config.yaml is a minimal, generated, comment-free slice
# (stacks + ci_cd.promotion_chain + test_policy only — no secrets, no local
# paths) that the CI workflows resolve at the checkout root. Regenerate with
# plugins/gaia/scripts/gen-ci-config.sh; a CI lint fails on drift.
!/.gaia/ci-config.yaml

# --- Build / test / coverage outputs ----------------------------------------
coverage/
err

# --- Perf baselines (E73-S2 /gaia-test-perf, environment-specific) ---------
.gaia/perf-baselines/

# --- Cluster 19 full-lifecycle per-run isolation dirs (E28-S133) ------------
plugins/gaia/test/runs/

# --- OS / editor artifacts --------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- Local environment ------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
*.log

# --- Config hydration runtime lock (E85-S1 / ADR-098) ----------------------
config/.config-hydration.lock

# --- E86-S2 ambient drift markers (NOT synced, runtime-only) --------------
# Canonical home is .gaia/memory/.framework-version-* (already covered by
# the global .gaia/ ignore at the top of this file).
